Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) seems likely as the paper deals with decidability of statements about winning conditions in games, which involves logical reasoning. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also likely as the paper deals with games and winning conditions. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could be a possible category as the paper introduces a way to parameterize automata and games on finite graphs with natural numbers, which involves algorithmic techniques. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with games and winning conditions, which are often studied in the context of AI. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper raises open questions regarding the complexity of boolean functions defined via graph game forms, which have properties akin to monotone circuits.
